                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='12' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='14' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='Dashboard 3' id='15' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='16' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='17' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='18' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='19' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='20' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='23' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='81390' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='96446' x='1683' y='17122'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='28'>BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE CAPSTONE PROJECT</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='17'>Æ </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='20'>Hospital Operational &amp;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='20'>Æ </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='20'>Financial Intelligence</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='20'>Æ </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Prepared by:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='24'>AmatulBaasit Ayomikun Ghazal</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='80893' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='4' type-v2='text' w='98130' x='873' y='18238'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#1b1b1b' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Project Objectives</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The objective of this investigation is to provide leadership with data-driven insights into capacity utilization, patient flow bottlenecks, clinical performance, and financial outcomes.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Findings from this analysis will support targeted operational improvements aimed at reducing unnecessary inpatient stays, optimizing bed utilization, lowering readmission rates, improving patient outcomes, and strengthening the hospital’s overall financial performance.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='79156' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='8' type-v2='text' w='98566' x='623' y='17866'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Monthly inpatient encounter volume across the 24-month analysis period ranged from a low of 65 to a high of 96 encounters per month, averaging approximately 79 encounters monthly. The trend reveals notable volatility without a clear directional pattern, suggesting that inpatient demand is irregular rather than systematically growing or declining. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The hospital&apos;s Average Length of Stay (ALOS) across all inpatient encounters is 4.9 days. Monthly ALOS fluctuates between 4.0 and 5.4 days, showing no consistent improvement over time. This persistent elevation above expected benchmarks is a central operational concern. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Inpatient volume volatility combined with a persistently elevated ALOS of 4.9 days suggests the hospital is not experiencing a demand surge. Still, rather than a throughput inefficiency, patients are staying longer than necessary, rather than more patients being admitted.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='73697' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='9' type-v2='text' w='97195' x='1683' y='22953'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Internal Medicine is the dominant inpatient department by a significant margin, handling over eight times the volume of Surgery and fifteen times that of O.G. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Critically, Internal Medicine is also the only department exceeding the hospital average ALOS of 4.9 days, recording 5.2 days, indicating that the department carrying the highest burden is also the least efficient in terms of patient throughput. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='76303' hidden='true' id='11' story-point-id='10' type-v2='text' w='97257' x='1434' y='21216'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The ten most frequently performed inpatient procedures reveal a clinical profile dominated by oncology, cardiac monitoring, and post-surgical care</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The high frequency of chemotherapy, CT chest, and respiratory support procedures is consistent with the significant volume of lung carcinoma patients identified in the clinical analysis. The volume of cardiac monitoring procedures (ECG, X-ray) aligns with the large number of cardiac and cardiovascular diagnoses in the inpatient population. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='79032' hidden='true' id='12' story-point-id='11' type-v2='text' w='97756' x='873' y='18362'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Together, the top two diagnoses: Dependent Drug Abuse and Non-Small Cell Lung Carcinoma account for nearly 45% of all inpatient admissions. Both diagnoses carry above-average ALOS (approximately 7 days each), placing them squarely in the high-burden zone of the clinical analysis. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Despite Dependent Drug Abuse being the highest-volume diagnosis at 437 encounters, it has a 0% 30-day readmission rate. This contrasts sharply with Non-Small Cell Lung Carcinoma, which has both high volume (420 encounters) and the highest readmission rate in the hospital (24.76%). These two diagnoses represent fundamentally different clinical challenges requiring distinct management strategies.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='75558' hidden='true' id='13' story-point-id='12' type-v2='text' w='97195' x='1122' y='20471'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Plotting diagnosis encounter volume against ALOS reveals a critical quadrant of diagnoses that combine high patient volume with above-average length of stay, the most resource-intensive clinical conditions in the hospital</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>High Burden Zone (above 4.9-day ALOS, above average volume):</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> Dependent Drug Abuse and Non-Small Cell Lung Carcinoma both sit in this quadrant, driving disproportionate resource consumption. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>High Volume, Efficient Zone (below 4.9-day ALOS, above average volume):</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> History of CABG (303 encounters, ~2 days ALOS), high throughput without excessive bed occupancy.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Complex, Rare Cases (above 4.9-day ALOS, low volume):</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> Several diagnoses with ALOS between 15–32 days appear in this zone, likely representing complex multi-morbidity cases requiring specialist management.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='77916' hidden='true' id='14' story-point-id='14' type-v2='text' w='97756' x='748' y='17122'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Readmission Analysis</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The hospital-wide 30-day readmission rate is 6.87%, representing 131 readmitted encounters out of 1,907 total inpatient encounters. While this rate is within a broadly acceptable range for a tertiary hospital, the distribution across diagnoses reveals a highly skewed pattern that demands targeted clinical intervention. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Non-Small Cell Lung Carcinoma accounts for 104 of the hospital&apos;s 131 total readmissions, representing 79.4% of all 30-day readmissions from a single diagnosis. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>With a readmission rate of 24.76%, one in four lung carcinoma patients returns to the hospital within 30 days of discharge. This is a significant patient safety and resource management concern that requires immediate clinical review.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The concentration of readmissions within oncology and specifically lung carcinoma suggests that current discharge protocols, post-discharge follow-up arrangements, and community support structures may be insufficient for this patient cohort.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The gap between the 6.87% overall rate and the 24.76% lung carcinoma rate indicates that the hospital average is being substantially suppressed by the zero-readmission rate for Dependent Drug Abuse patients.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='80769' hidden='true' id='15' story-point-id='16' type-v2='text' w='98130' x='810' y='16873'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Total inpatient charges over the 24-month analysis period amounted to $43.32M, with insurance payments covering $41.23M (95.18%) and patient out-of-pocket payments contributing $2.09M (4.82%). This near-complete dependence on insurance funding represents both a structural characteristic and a financial risk factor for the hospital. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='79529' hidden='true' id='16' story-point-id='17' type-v2='text' w='97693' x='1309' y='17122'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Monthly inpatient charges show a clear declining trend across the analysis period. Total charges peaked at $2.9M in January 2023 and again in June 2023 before declining persistently through 2024, reaching a low of $1.1M in December 2024, a reduction of approximately 62% from peak to trough. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Æ  </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The monthly average charge across the full period is $1.80M. The consistent downward trajectory in the latter half of the analysis period is concerning, as it suggests a structural decline in revenue-generating activity rather than seasonal variation. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Inpatient charges declined by 62% from peak ($2.9M) to December 2024 ($1.1M). This trend, combined with stable or increasing operational costs associated with prolonged ALOS and readmissions, points to a widening gap between operational burden and financial return, a pattern that is unsustainable without intervention.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='79404' hidden='true' id='17' story-point-id='18' type-v2='text' w='98005' x='935' y='18983'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Both insurance payments and patient payments follow a declining trend broadly consistent with the total charges trajectory. Insurance payments average $1.7M monthly while patient payments average $87.1K monthly, a ratio of approximately 20:1.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The January 2024 spike in patient payments ($202.9K) is an outlier that warrants further investigation into billing or coding practices in that period. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='80397' hidden='true' id='18' story-point-id='19' type-v2='text' w='97631' x='1185' y='17246'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Financial performance mirrors the operational workload concentration identified in the operational analysis</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Internal Medicine generates 91.9% of total inpatient charges, consistent with its 85.5% share of encounter volume. However, the revenue per encounter of $24,540 for Internal Medicine reflects the complexity and cost of managing oncology, cardiac, and substance abuse patients.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Surgery generates a lower total revenue but a relatively high revenue per encounter at $16,071, reflecting the procedural nature of surgical admissions. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='79032' hidden='true' id='19' story-point-id='20' type-v2='text' w='96758' x='998' y='18610'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Recommendations</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Establish Internal Medicine Capacity Review Committee</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Implement Structured Discharge Planning Protocols</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Review Oncology Procedure Scheduling (Inpatient vs. Day-Case)</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Implement Lung Carcinoma Post-Discharge Surveillance Programme</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Develop a Substance Abuse to Community Care Transition Pathway</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Establish Cardiac Readmission Prevention Protocols</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Investigate the Root Cause of Declining Inpatient Charges</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Reduce Insurance Dependency Through Payer Diversification</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='81390' hidden='true' id='20' story-point-id='22' type-v2='text' w='96446' x='1683' y='17122'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Executive Summary</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The hospital is a large tertiary care institution providing complex, specialist inpatient services across</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>multiple clinical departments. Over the past two years, hospital leadership has raised concerns </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>across five key operational areas: </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Æ  </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       Prolonged inpatient stays exceeding expected benchmarks </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       Increasing bed occupancy pressure and reduced patient throughput </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       Delayed patient turnover affecting departmental capacity </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       Rising 30-day readmission rates suggest gaps in discharge planning </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•       Growing financial strain despite sustained levels of patient activity </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Æ  </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Leadership commissioned this investigation to provide a data-driven assessment of hospital performance, identify systemic pressure points, and support evidence-based decision-making at the executive level. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>All analyses were conducted on inpatient encounters only.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>The analysis period covers January 2023 to December 2024, the most recent 24 months of the hospital activity, to ensure findings are operationally relevant and actionable. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='17'>Æ  </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='76303' hidden='true' id='21' story-point-id='23' type-v2='text' w='98815' x='436' y='17246'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='16'>Conclusions</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>This investigation has surfaced a hospital system operating under concentrated, manageable, and addressable pressure. The findings do not indicate a systemic collapse but rather a set of identifiable bottlenecks that, if left unaddressed, will compound into more serious operational and financial challenges. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Three themes emerge consistently across the operational, clinical, and financial analyses:</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•  </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Concentration risk:</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> A single department (Internal Medicine), two diagnoses (Lung Carcinoma and Drug Abuse), and one payer type (insurance) account for the disproportionate share of hospital activity and revenue. This concentration creates vulnerability. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•   </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Throughput inefficiency:</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> Elevated ALOS and high readmission rates in specific diagnoses suggest that patients are not transitioning efficiently through the care pathway, from admission, through treatment, to discharge and community support. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>•   </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Financial sustainability concern:</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> The 62% decline in monthly inpatient charges over the analysis period, occurring alongside stable operational burdens, is not consistent with a financially healthy</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>trajectory and requires urgent executive attention. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{00C7033B-58A2-4513-AD6B-D87B9EB51C2B}' />
    </dashboard>
